# $_COOKIE Superglobal

Cookies sent by the browser are available in the `$_COOKIE` associative array.

```php
if (isset($_COOKIE['theme'])) {
    $theme = $_COOKIE['theme'];
} else {
    $theme = 'light'; // default
}
```

Note: `$_COOKIE` is populated only **after** the cookie is received from the browser. A cookie set in the current request will not be available in `$_COOKIE` until the next page load.
